    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nThis is a blocker for Nvim 0.12 release\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nThe new UI events `restart`, `connect`, etc. should be future-proof.\n\nSpecifically, it seems important that `restart` includes the address of the new Nvim https://github.com/neovim/neovim/pull/34367 . I know that @zeertzjq has mentioned some challenges , such as:\n\n> If the server is running with `--listen` on a socket and the client is attached to that socket, the new server cannot be started until the old server stop listening on the socket. But if the old server stops listening, the client cannot notify it.\n\nbut there is a big benefit to putting the address in the event: the logic can mostly live in the server. This especially matters for emitting \"p2p\" events to other discovered Nvims. Asking each GUI to implement that logic, is cumbersome.",
